         <div type="commentary" subtype="frontmatter" xml:space="preserve">
        <p>Medical prescriptions for cicatrizing plasters (P.Aberd. 10). Papyrus fragment (10.5 x 5.1 cm) complete at the top and broken off on the other three sides. It preserves remains of at least four recipes of cicatrizing plasters (ἐπουλωτικαί) arranged with headings in ekthesis and blank spaces at the end of the last line.</p>
        <p>
          <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en">This papyrus has been digitally edited by Nicola Reggiani as part of the Project "DIGMEDTEXT - Online Humanities Scholarship: A Digital Medical Library based on Ancient Texts" (ERC-AdG-2013, Grant Agreement no. 339828) funded by the European Research Council at the University of Parma (Principal Investigator: Prof. Isabella Andorlini). The digital edition is mostly based on the previous editions: E.O. Winstedt, CQ 1 (1907), p. 265 top [diplomatic transcription]; E.G. Turner, P.Aberd. 10 (1939); C. Calame, Actes IVe Coll. int. hipp. [Lausanne 1981] (1983), 132-4 = REG 97 (1984), 206-13; I. Andorlini, Ricette mediche nei papiri (1981) = Scritti I, 2017, 68-74</note>
        </p>
